The trial division method is a simple and straightforward approach to determine whether a number is prime. The method involves dividing the number by each integer from 2 to the square root of the number, and checking if it is divisible. If it is divisible, then it is not prime. If it is not divisible, then it is prime. Here is an example of how to implement this method in Python:
