### 2. Sieve of Eratosthenes Method

The Sieve of Eratosthenes is a more efficient method for determining whether a number is prime. The method works by creating a list of all numbers up to the number to be tested, and then iteratively marking as composite (i.e., not prime) any number that is divisible by a prime number less than or equal to the square root of the number. The remaining numbers in the list are the prime numbers. Here is an example of how to implement this method in Python:
